Dr. Jill Biden is traveling to San Jose, Costa Rica as part of her four-country visit to Central and South America. Her visit aims to engage government and civil society partners on issues related to economic empowerment and educational opportunities for women and girls. Dr. Biden will also visit Lima and Cusco in Peru, Buenos Aires and Tucuman in Argentina, and Panama City in Panama. She will raise awareness for girls' education and women's empowerment through her Medium account and social media. In Costa Rica, Dr. Biden will visit Universidad Tecnica Nacional and deliver remarks on advancing gender equality in education. She will also visit Hogar Siembra, a safe house for young women, and meet the girls benefiting from various programs. After her visit to Costa Rica, Dr. Biden will depart for Lima, Peru.